WEBVTT

00:02.269 --> 00:03.003
(Briggs)
Previously on Graceland...

00:04.238 --> 00:06.273
I made a call,
some of my old Mexican contacts.

00:06.273 --> 00:07.541
(Mike)
What contacts?

00:07.541 --> 00:10.277
The kind that put me in touch
with Caza cartel leadership.

00:10.277 --> 00:12.112
[shouts]

00:13.146 --> 00:14.147
(Tuturro)
Lucia!

00:14.181 --> 00:16.650
(Carlito)
If I die, she dies.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.685
[gunshot]
- Ah!

00:18.685 --> 00:20.420
That's a good boy, Johnny.

00:20.454 --> 00:24.224
These birds and the numbers,
they mean something,

00:24.258 --> 00:27.561
and I was sent back here
to figure out what.

00:27.594 --> 00:29.429
(Briggs)
Let's shut the book
on Ari Adamian.

00:29.429 --> 00:30.497
I need you.

00:30.531 --> 00:32.299
Start to finish,
this takes 24 hours.

00:32.299 --> 00:33.767
How do you imagine
this ending?

00:33.967 --> 00:35.502
With Ari no longer
a threat to living.

00:35.536 --> 00:38.438
[dramatic music]

00:38.472 --> 00:40.040
♪ ♪

00:40.040 --> 00:45.312
(Ari)
There's only one man
in the entire world...

00:45.312 --> 00:49.716
one man who knew enough
to make all this shit up.

00:49.716 --> 00:50.717
Colby.

00:50.751 --> 00:53.086
We got to have
a little talk.

00:59.760 --> 01:03.196
So Martun did this?

01:03.230 --> 01:08.702
It's an ugly way to go,
but he deserve worse.

01:08.735 --> 01:10.571
And Colby never said
anything to you

01:10.571 --> 01:12.506
about how he wanted Layla
for himself?

01:12.539 --> 01:15.042
Ari, come on, man.

01:15.075 --> 01:18.178
Whatever was in Colby's head,
whatever this was,

01:18.211 --> 01:20.314
whatever this is,
I have no idea.

01:20.347 --> 01:24.217
Your one friend
in this sunburn city betrays me,

01:24.217 --> 01:26.219
and you got no idea?

01:26.253 --> 01:28.088
Hmm.

01:30.657 --> 01:32.225
I could have died.

01:32.225 --> 01:35.662
I drop that match,
Martun give me that bath.

01:37.598 --> 01:39.166
Ari, think about this.

01:39.199 --> 01:42.469
How could I have anything
to do with this, Ari?

01:42.469 --> 01:44.438
Think about it.
I was with you at Nancy's.

01:44.471 --> 01:45.739
Then I was at the laundromat,
and then I was with you.

01:45.973 --> 01:47.708
When Martun put his gun
to the side of my head,

01:47.741 --> 01:49.743
did I throw you under the bus
to save my own ass?

01:49.743 --> 01:52.379
No, the hell I did not.

01:54.181 --> 01:57.184
[clicks tongue]
That's what I said.

01:59.086 --> 02:01.655
But Martun, he wanted
to ask Colby for himself.

02:01.688 --> 02:04.458
Guess he didn't want to disturb
the neighbors with screaming,

02:04.491 --> 02:08.495
so he had him write down
the names of his accomplices.

02:09.663 --> 02:13.500
[sighs]
Jesus.

02:14.968 --> 02:19.573
Okay.
So what now, boss?

02:19.606 --> 02:22.609
Now what?

02:22.643 --> 02:26.647
Now the truth has come out
about me and Layla,

02:26.680 --> 02:31.518
and Martun is not so happy
with me,

02:31.518 --> 02:35.355
so Toros will take over

02:35.389 --> 02:38.392
a lot of my business.

02:38.425 --> 02:42.663
Okay, so we do what we gotta do
to get you back on top.

02:42.696 --> 02:48.001
You--you don't work for me
anymore.

02:48.001 --> 02:50.270
Colby gave up no one,
but you, man,

02:50.270 --> 02:52.472
you still got his stink

02:52.506 --> 02:54.508
all over you.

02:56.043 --> 03:00.280
If I ever see you again,
I'm gonna kill you.

03:03.717 --> 03:06.687
[hip-hop music]

03:06.720 --> 03:09.489
♪ ♪

03:09.523 --> 03:13.660
(Logan)
I just don't get why Colby
kidnapped Sarkissian's daughter.

03:13.694 --> 03:16.630
All I know is
what Ari told me.

03:16.663 --> 03:18.665
Colby tried to frame him
for her murder.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.534
That's not his style.

03:20.567 --> 03:23.270
Can we tag Martun
with the homicide?

03:23.270 --> 03:24.471
Nah.

03:26.473 --> 03:29.376
[sighs]
All right.

03:29.409 --> 03:31.578
Ari will be in handcuffs today.

03:31.578 --> 03:34.014
He's in no position to be
second in command anymore.

03:34.047 --> 03:35.148
He's useless.

03:35.182 --> 03:36.683
What?

03:36.717 --> 03:38.318
You let him
torture and kill,

03:38.351 --> 03:39.319
and the minute
we hit a speed bump,

03:39.319 --> 03:40.387
you're ready to jump ship?

03:40.420 --> 03:42.589
This is not a speed bump,
Briggs.

03:42.622 --> 03:43.724
It's a dead agent.

03:43.757 --> 03:45.525
Right.

03:45.559 --> 03:48.028
What happened to
"thousands of people die

03:48.061 --> 03:50.297
every day from the arms provided
by the Sarkissians"? What--

03:50.330 --> 03:51.732
You're gonna take heat
on the O'Malley murder

03:51.732 --> 03:52.999
when Ari goes to trial.

03:53.033 --> 03:54.134
We'll get you a good lawyer,

03:54.167 --> 03:55.435
shoot for soft time.

03:55.469 --> 03:57.304
The Badillo murder tape
disappears.

03:57.304 --> 03:59.439
And what about Martun,
hmm?

03:59.473 --> 04:01.174
You care so much about Colby.

04:01.174 --> 04:03.577
He's the one who did this.

04:03.577 --> 04:05.512
I could give a shit
about the Badillo murder tape.

04:05.545 --> 04:08.081
You wanted a sin-eater,
well, you've got one.

04:08.081 --> 04:10.350
So go ahead, Logan.
Ladle it on.

04:10.350 --> 04:14.054
Give me seconds. Give me thirds.
I will lick the plate.

04:14.087 --> 04:17.090
I'll ride Ari all the way up,
no matter what mayhem it brings.

04:17.090 --> 04:21.094
I'm not walking away,
not until Martun is done.

04:21.128 --> 04:23.463
Watch your back.

04:27.734 --> 04:30.070
Damn.
No, okay, thank you.

04:30.070 --> 04:31.171
Well, no, no, no,

04:31.204 --> 04:32.205
you ain't gotta put
anything official out.

04:32.205 --> 04:35.208
He's probably
just sleeping one off.

04:35.242 --> 04:36.476
[chuckles]

04:36.510 --> 04:38.078
Thanks.

04:38.078 --> 04:39.713
No hospitals,
no coroner's office.

04:39.746 --> 04:41.481
It's been six hours
and nothing.

04:41.481 --> 04:43.717
You need to put out a BOLO,
get agents looking.

04:43.750 --> 04:46.019
Yeah, we put out a BOLO,
then we gotta explain

04:46.052 --> 04:48.622
our involvement--
all our involvement--

04:48.655 --> 04:50.390
so maybe we just
give him some time.

04:50.390 --> 04:51.525
- How much time?
[door opens]

04:51.558 --> 04:53.627
- Ari took him, Jakes.
[door closes]

04:53.660 --> 04:56.129
(Charlie)
W--thank God!

04:56.163 --> 04:57.664
The hell?

04:57.697 --> 05:00.300
Where the hell were you, man,
and what happened with Ari?

05:02.502 --> 05:06.973
Uh...
it didn't go as planned.

05:07.007 --> 05:09.109
Colby's dead, guys.

05:12.112 --> 05:15.115
It was perfect--
perfect right up until the end,

05:15.115 --> 05:19.519
and then, uh,
Ari figured it out.

05:19.519 --> 05:22.088
We burned the fingers
on the wrong hand.

05:22.122 --> 05:23.223
Ari got onto it.

05:23.256 --> 05:24.624
He convinced Martun

05:24.658 --> 05:26.459
that Colby was
trying to framing him.

05:26.493 --> 05:29.462
Martun stripped Colby naked
and tortured him to death--

05:29.496 --> 05:33.166
battery acid.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.602
He never gave me up,
right up until the end.

05:35.635 --> 05:38.538
So he murdered Colby.
Bring Sarkissian in.

05:38.538 --> 05:40.140
- It's not that simple.
- How isn't that--

05:40.140 --> 05:41.274
'Cause we don't have
enough evidence

05:41.308 --> 05:42.642
to pin him to the murder,
but rest assured,

05:42.676 --> 05:44.344
we're gonna bring his ass in
one way or the other.

05:44.377 --> 05:45.645
Who's "we"?

05:45.679 --> 05:50.350
D.J., if we walk away now,
Martun skates.

05:50.383 --> 05:52.085
The point of this was
to get you away from Ari, Paul.

05:52.118 --> 05:54.154
Martun killed Colby.

05:54.154 --> 05:56.489
No, P, nah,
we killed Colby.

05:56.523 --> 05:59.092
This stupid-ass plan
killed Colby.

05:59.125 --> 06:00.627
I love you, man,
but you keep running on this,

06:00.660 --> 06:01.628
it's on you.
I'm out.

06:01.661 --> 06:02.696
This isn't just about me.

06:02.696 --> 06:05.365
No, it is.
It's all about you.

06:05.398 --> 06:06.700
We don't do our jobs
anymore.

06:06.733 --> 06:09.669
We don't bust bad guys anymore.
Something's not working.

06:09.669 --> 06:12.305
Which is precisely why
we need to stay the course, D.J.

06:12.339 --> 06:14.307
Now, look, Logan was ready
to pull the plug, but no.

06:14.341 --> 06:16.676
No, I say perp walks and cavity
searches for all those bitches.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.178
Wait, wait, wait,
you had an out?

06:18.178 --> 06:19.312
Why didn't you take it?

06:19.346 --> 06:20.447
Because then we wouldn't
have justice, Chuck.

06:20.480 --> 06:22.315
Justice?

06:22.315 --> 06:24.317
When do we ever
have justice?

06:24.351 --> 06:28.188
Everything we do
ends up with a body.

06:28.188 --> 06:31.691
This has got to stop.

06:44.437 --> 06:45.405
What's the plan?

06:45.438 --> 06:47.574
Hmm?

06:47.574 --> 06:50.543
To get Martun.
What's the plan?

06:50.577 --> 06:53.747
[sighs]
I don't know.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.049
I'm still working it out.

07:00.754 --> 07:03.757
[electronic music]

07:03.757 --> 07:09.996
♪ ♪

07:20.640 --> 07:22.609
[knocking at the door]

07:22.609 --> 07:24.577
[door opens and closes]

07:31.618 --> 07:35.088
It was a mistake, Mike.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.656
If you're looking
for absolution--

07:36.656 --> 07:40.393
I'm not, man.

07:40.393 --> 07:41.628
I'm looking
for enlightenment.

07:41.661 --> 07:44.664
Enlightenment?
Mystic man.

07:44.664 --> 07:47.500
Talking all that Bardo shit,
levels of salvation.

07:47.534 --> 07:49.736
[scoffs]

07:51.972 --> 07:55.642
Maybe it's all bullshit.

07:55.675 --> 07:58.378
You know, I give you words,

07:58.378 --> 08:01.514
I give you speeches, but...

08:01.548 --> 08:05.719
underneath it all,
it's just guesses,

08:05.752 --> 08:08.221
hope, fear.

08:08.254 --> 08:11.725
The best of us are looking
through that mirror darkly,

08:11.758 --> 08:12.726
but not you.

08:12.759 --> 08:15.996
Y-you were there.

08:16.029 --> 08:19.532
Convince me
that there was more

08:19.566 --> 08:21.401
to Colby's last moments
on this earth

08:21.401 --> 08:24.004
than meaningless suffering.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.339
Okay, okay.

08:31.978 --> 08:35.648
Where I was,
there wasn't any pain,

08:35.682 --> 08:39.352
but the rest of it,
I can't help you with.

08:39.386 --> 08:43.490
I-I'm sitting here
looking up red birds and numbers

08:43.523 --> 08:44.424
on the Internet.

08:44.457 --> 08:46.292
[chuckles]

08:46.326 --> 08:48.161
Oh, did you know
that the cardinal is considered

08:48.194 --> 08:49.562
a matchmaker to the Choctaw?

08:49.596 --> 08:51.398
Something I don't
give a shit about.

08:51.431 --> 08:54.401
You know the name Adam is used
47 times in the Bible?

08:54.401 --> 08:58.271
47 is also the country code
of Norway.

08:58.304 --> 09:01.307
I don't know anything.

09:01.307 --> 09:03.576
Maybe the universe doesn't
always hang signposts

09:03.610 --> 09:07.313
in a language that
we understand, you know?

09:07.313 --> 09:08.681
Do you honestly believe

09:08.715 --> 09:11.584
that there's some purpose
to all this?

09:11.618 --> 09:13.453
Mike, you were given
a vision.

09:13.453 --> 09:17.724
I choose to believe
that we are all put on a path.

09:17.724 --> 09:20.326
We might not want it,
we might not like it,

09:20.326 --> 09:22.595
we might not even understand
the shit,

09:22.595 --> 09:25.732
but still,
our path is our path.

09:25.732 --> 09:27.267
[chuckles]

09:28.701 --> 09:31.271
Stay on that path,
young man.

09:36.476 --> 09:39.446
[alternative rock music]

09:39.479 --> 09:47.520
♪ ♪

10:39.506 --> 10:42.509
[alarm beeping]

10:43.610 --> 10:44.611
Chuck, wake up!

10:44.644 --> 10:46.346
- Jesus. Oh, shit.
- Oh! Ah.

10:46.379 --> 10:47.480
- Okay.
- Shit.

10:47.514 --> 10:49.649
Can somebody please turn
that thing off? Just--

10:49.682 --> 10:51.618
What is that smell?

10:51.651 --> 10:52.752
- [coughs]
- Ah!

10:52.986 --> 10:54.621
It's nothing.
It's fine.

10:54.654 --> 10:57.257
Smoke alarms at the ass crack
of dawn is not fine.

10:57.290 --> 11:00.727
So it's 6:00 a.m.,
and you decided to cook...

11:00.760 --> 11:03.363
Tuna freakin' casserole.
Chuck, are you serious?

11:03.396 --> 11:06.166
Guys, I'm tired,
and I'm sick of airplane food,

11:06.166 --> 11:08.401
so forgive me for wanting
a decent breakfast.

11:08.434 --> 11:12.238
Tuna casserole
is not breakfast.

11:12.272 --> 11:13.373
Come on.

11:13.406 --> 11:14.541
[alarm stops]
- Thank you.

11:14.574 --> 11:16.409
Tall-ass ceilings.

11:16.442 --> 11:18.411
I think you might need
to slow down a little.

11:18.411 --> 11:21.548
No, I have to get Germaine.
There's no slowing down.

11:21.548 --> 11:22.682
You know,
running yourself ragged

11:22.715 --> 11:24.350
and burning the house down
in the process

11:24.384 --> 11:25.552
is not gonna help you
catch him, Chuck.

11:25.552 --> 11:27.153
Yeah, well--

11:27.187 --> 11:29.522
Guys, I found it.

11:29.556 --> 11:31.991
This about your crazy birds
and numbers?

11:32.025 --> 11:33.426
He's not crazy, Jakes.

11:33.426 --> 11:35.662
I didn't say he was crazy,
but these birds and numbers

11:35.695 --> 11:36.696
getting a little crazy.

11:36.696 --> 11:38.565
None of it's crazy.

11:38.565 --> 11:40.433
I've been upstairs working
on this the past couple days.

11:40.433 --> 11:42.101
It's been--
it's been ten days.

11:42.135 --> 11:43.336
Just listen.

11:43.369 --> 11:45.104
I've been tracking an exchange
on DarkMarquet.

11:45.138 --> 11:47.574
It's an undisclosed parcel
pickup here in Los Angeles

11:47.607 --> 11:50.310
between two parties,
VinXXX and Huma9.

11:50.310 --> 11:55.048
VinXXX: V is the shape
the clock hands make at 10:10.

11:55.081 --> 11:56.249
X--

11:56.282 --> 11:57.684
Roman numeral for ten.

11:57.717 --> 12:00.587
Right, but Huma9
is the real prize.

12:00.587 --> 12:02.021
The Huma's
a mythological creature.

12:02.055 --> 12:03.456
It's the Persian equivalent
of the Phoenix,

12:03.489 --> 12:05.325
and when this bird
rises from its ashes,

12:05.325 --> 12:07.060
I'll give you one guess
what color it is.

12:07.093 --> 12:08.194
You found your red bird.

12:08.194 --> 12:10.697
Yeah.

12:10.730 --> 12:13.466
Okay,
I know it's a stretch,

12:13.499 --> 12:16.002
and I wouldn't have even
dug in until this.

12:16.035 --> 12:18.304
VinXXX got pickup details
this morning.

12:18.304 --> 12:20.306
His parcel is
on a container ship,

12:20.306 --> 12:24.410
and the shipping container
that it's in is number 11-47-11.

12:24.444 --> 12:25.411
47.

12:25.445 --> 12:26.546
It's all here,

12:26.579 --> 12:29.716
47, the red birds,
even the clock hands.

12:33.086 --> 12:35.021
Okay.

12:35.054 --> 12:37.757
It's just--it's a little early
for all of this.

12:37.991 --> 12:40.760
I'm gonna make you
a proper breakfast.

12:40.994 --> 12:42.328
(Charlie)
Coffee.

12:42.362 --> 12:44.697
Yeah, when your birds and
numbers turn into a real case,

12:44.731 --> 12:45.698
call me, man.

12:45.732 --> 12:46.699
You got my number.

12:46.733 --> 12:48.301
Yeah.

12:48.334 --> 12:51.304
And I got other shit
to do.

12:53.339 --> 12:55.708
It's impressive, Mike,

12:55.742 --> 12:58.278
but you know you can't
take that to the FBI.

12:58.311 --> 13:00.480
No, not yet.

13:00.513 --> 13:03.216
I need your help,
Briggs.

13:03.216 --> 13:06.586
The ship docks at 7:00.

13:06.619 --> 13:09.589
Yeah.
Yeah, I'll be there.

13:11.391 --> 13:13.359
Good job.

13:18.998 --> 13:20.266
You shouldn't be in here,
Johnny.

13:20.266 --> 13:21.234
We gotta talk.

13:21.234 --> 13:22.502
We will, soon.

13:22.502 --> 13:25.238
Ah, bro, hey,
we're way past soon, man.

13:25.238 --> 13:28.107
I told you I'd help you
get Lucia away from Carlito,

13:28.141 --> 13:30.510
and I'm handling it
right now.

13:30.510 --> 13:33.346
I'm looking right at you, man.
How are you handling it?

13:33.379 --> 13:35.515
You know, Johnny,
not everything that's happening

13:35.548 --> 13:37.684
is happening
in front of you.

13:38.685 --> 13:41.087
[sighs]

13:41.120 --> 13:44.691
[horn blares]

13:47.093 --> 13:48.361
Catch anything yet?

13:48.394 --> 13:49.662
Longshoremen unloaded
our shipping container

13:49.696 --> 13:52.432
about an hour ago,
dropped it in stack 14.

13:52.465 --> 13:54.000
Got it.

13:54.033 --> 13:55.401
The BIC code
on that container,

13:55.401 --> 13:57.270
it's just some
unaffiliated holding company.

13:57.270 --> 14:00.006
There's no address
on record.

14:00.006 --> 14:03.009
Oh, look at that,
looks like our boy VinXXX

14:03.009 --> 14:05.511
is keeping
the same hours as you.

14:05.545 --> 14:08.348
Wait.
Who the hell is that?

14:08.381 --> 14:09.415
What, that's not
your guy?

14:09.415 --> 14:11.017
I mean, it's a guy,
but that's a kid.

14:11.017 --> 14:12.151
How old do you think he is?

14:12.151 --> 14:13.519
Early 20s,
but what's the difference?

14:13.553 --> 14:16.522
I mean, kids break the law
same as adults, Mike.

14:18.191 --> 14:20.660
Come on.
No.

14:20.693 --> 14:23.029
God, this is all wrong.

14:23.062 --> 14:24.564
Well, he's certainly not
a professional,

14:24.597 --> 14:25.698
but what the hell
were you expecting?

14:25.698 --> 14:27.400
Something bigger,
I don't know.

14:27.433 --> 14:29.969
God, not this.

14:30.002 --> 14:32.305
What's your play?

14:32.338 --> 14:34.574
Let's follow him,

14:34.574 --> 14:38.277
see where he's going
with that stuff.

14:38.311 --> 14:40.380
It's just, it doesn't
make any sense.

14:40.413 --> 14:42.582
The kid picks up a shipment,
and then he goes bowling?

14:42.582 --> 14:44.684
Yeah.
Well, you know, Big D's,

14:44.717 --> 14:46.586
it's a loud,
cheap loitering spot,

14:46.586 --> 14:49.122
perfect for scammers
and hustlers to pick up work

14:49.155 --> 14:50.456
and not get caught.

14:50.490 --> 14:51.991
Oh, so our kid's
a small-timer?

14:52.024 --> 14:53.726
Looks like it. He certainly
isn't Pablo Escobar.

14:53.760 --> 14:57.063
What do you want to do,
pick him up?

14:57.063 --> 14:59.465
I want to go under,
meet this kid.

14:59.465 --> 15:00.566
I want find out
what's in that trunk

15:00.600 --> 15:03.002
and where
he's bringing it.

15:03.035 --> 15:06.139
You ever wonder if maybe,
just maybe,

15:06.172 --> 15:07.707
the bird you're chasing
might be a wild goose?

15:07.707 --> 15:11.310
Yeah, of course,
but I'm staying on the path,

15:11.310 --> 15:13.079
and I'm gonna see
where this thing ends.

15:18.351 --> 15:21.354
Okay, Gusti Kadek Pendit.

15:21.354 --> 15:22.688
Got his green card
about three years ago.

15:22.722 --> 15:24.757
Our boy's from Manggis, Bali.
He's Indonesian.

15:24.991 --> 15:26.759
Uh, Balinese, to be exact.

15:26.993 --> 15:28.761
Bali's an Indonesian island,
so--

15:28.995 --> 15:31.164
Yes, same country,
separate people.

15:31.197 --> 15:33.232
Bali's got its own culture,
its own history.

15:33.232 --> 15:36.269
Fine, he's Balinese.
He's also a repeat offender.

15:36.302 --> 15:38.738
Mm-hmm, trespassing,
petty theft,

15:38.738 --> 15:40.740
receipt of stolen property,
vandalism.

15:40.740 --> 15:43.609
[laughs] You see this?
Hollywood Stunt Academy?

15:43.643 --> 15:45.077
Yeah, yeah.

15:45.077 --> 15:47.180
Our boy wants to be
in the pictures.

15:47.213 --> 15:48.347
Says he flunked out.

15:48.347 --> 15:49.449
Twice.

15:49.482 --> 15:51.150
Hmm.

15:51.184 --> 15:54.620
So we have got
a Balinese immigrant

15:54.620 --> 15:57.256
who can't take a punch.

15:57.256 --> 15:58.491
What are you thinking?

15:58.524 --> 16:00.092
Honestly?

16:00.126 --> 16:02.495
I think I flash any cash,
this kid's my best friend.

16:02.528 --> 16:05.398
Hmm.
He's a grifter, though, Mike.

16:05.431 --> 16:06.599
You know,
you show up loaded,

16:06.632 --> 16:08.167
he may see you more as a mark
than a friend.

16:08.201 --> 16:11.637
Yeah.
So I come in at his level.

16:11.637 --> 16:14.240
Maybe below.

16:14.240 --> 16:15.641
[chuckles]

16:15.641 --> 16:16.976
So you want to run this
with me?

16:16.976 --> 16:19.979
Jakes has been looking
for a real case.

16:20.012 --> 16:22.448
I'ma tell him
shit just got real.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.116
Where you going?

16:24.150 --> 16:27.386
It's been over a week
since I've seen our boy Ari.

16:27.386 --> 16:29.188
I'm gonna pay him a visit.

16:39.432 --> 16:42.401
[Middle Eastern music]

16:42.401 --> 16:43.402
♪ ♪

16:43.402 --> 16:44.403
[doorbell jingles]

16:44.403 --> 16:46.372
[Ari humming with music]

16:46.405 --> 16:48.674
I do my singing alone
in the shower.

16:48.708 --> 16:52.011
Told you if I saw you again,
I'm gonna kill you.

16:52.011 --> 16:55.248
Yes, you did.

16:55.281 --> 16:56.983
Brought you
a little something.

16:57.016 --> 16:59.252
Check it out.

17:00.453 --> 17:03.756
It's clean, filed down,
brand-new suppressor.

17:03.990 --> 17:05.358
You know, if you were
going to shoot me,

17:05.391 --> 17:07.360
that would be
a great burner to use.

17:12.565 --> 17:15.134
What?
You want to die?

17:15.134 --> 17:16.502
[laughs]

17:16.536 --> 17:18.538
No, Ari,
I don't want to die.

17:18.571 --> 17:20.172
I want to make money,
you dumb ass.

17:20.206 --> 17:21.307
You forget who I am?

17:21.307 --> 17:23.442
- Whoa. No, no.
- Hmm?

17:23.442 --> 17:24.710
How could I ever
forget you, Ari?

17:24.710 --> 17:27.313
I know exactly who you are,

17:27.346 --> 17:28.447
and that's the problem,
isn't it?

17:28.481 --> 17:31.250
Yeah, loose ends,
it's bad business.

17:31.284 --> 17:35.688
But two things I am not
are an idiot or a coward.

17:35.721 --> 17:37.323
I'm not gonna spend
the rest of my life

17:37.356 --> 17:38.658
looking over my shoulder,

17:38.691 --> 17:40.326
waiting for your bullet
to show up.

17:40.326 --> 17:41.661
When death comes
knocking on my door,

17:41.694 --> 17:44.697
I'm gonna look that bitch
right in the eye.

17:44.730 --> 17:47.700
There's no nobility
in death.

17:51.404 --> 17:53.005
So what is the real reason?

17:53.039 --> 17:54.307
Let me break it down
for you.

17:54.307 --> 17:56.042
Okay.
[clears throat]

17:56.075 --> 18:00.046
You know what
the beauty of war is, Ari?

18:00.079 --> 18:03.549
It is always
a prime investment.

18:03.583 --> 18:05.585
You never go
out of business.

18:05.618 --> 18:08.354
Now, I signed up to work
for your sorry ass

18:08.354 --> 18:11.424
because you happen to have
a pie that I want a piece of.

18:11.457 --> 18:13.559
There is no pie!

18:13.593 --> 18:16.362
Martun forgets
all the work I did for him,

18:16.362 --> 18:19.632
and my uncle,
he bites his fat tongue.

18:19.632 --> 18:21.601
The fun is over.

18:21.634 --> 18:23.202
You know, Ari, I thought
you were the real deal,

18:23.235 --> 18:25.438
but I guess not.

18:25.471 --> 18:26.439
Huh.

18:26.472 --> 18:28.341
Let me help you out.

18:28.374 --> 18:31.277
Clean up your shit!

18:31.310 --> 18:33.579
If you don't have the sack
to step up

18:33.613 --> 18:36.415
and take what's yours,
if you don't trust me

18:36.449 --> 18:37.717
after everything
I have done for you,

18:37.750 --> 18:39.018
then you know what, man?

18:39.051 --> 18:40.753
Do me a favor
and blow me away right now.

18:40.987 --> 18:41.988
You are stupid.

18:42.021 --> 18:43.389
Do it, Ari.
Do it, Ari.

18:43.422 --> 18:44.457
Do it!

18:44.490 --> 18:45.591
[laughs]

18:45.625 --> 18:48.628
You're a lunatic, man.

18:49.629 --> 18:50.596
[laughs]

18:50.630 --> 18:51.664
Let's have a drink.

18:51.664 --> 18:52.665
[puts gun down]

18:52.665 --> 18:54.634
Why the hell not?

18:55.635 --> 18:57.970
Yeah, I'ma tell you,
homeboy,

18:57.970 --> 19:00.239
in the '90s you couldn't jack
them cars fast enough, man.

19:00.239 --> 19:03.376
Everybody wanted
that hot tape deck,

19:03.376 --> 19:06.312
that hot stereo, you know,
but nowadays,

19:06.345 --> 19:08.247
the factory issue's
just as good

19:08.247 --> 19:10.116
as the high-end shit,
you feel me?

19:10.149 --> 19:11.317
You're trying to rip me off
right now.

19:11.350 --> 19:12.485
Hey, whoa, relax, man.

19:12.518 --> 19:15.121
Ain't nobody trying
to rip nobody off.

19:15.121 --> 19:16.389
Trying to give you,
like, 100.

19:16.389 --> 19:18.124
I get 110 retail,
asshole.

19:18.157 --> 19:21.127
And I'm offering you
100 each, asshole.

19:23.129 --> 19:24.563
- All right. Yeah.
- Yeah, we good?

19:24.563 --> 19:25.998
Let me go to my car
real quick.

19:26.032 --> 19:28.067
- All right.
- Stay.

19:34.373 --> 19:37.510
Hey, your friend,
he's a cop.

19:37.543 --> 19:38.511
Excuse me?

19:38.544 --> 19:41.347
Police.
What kind of stereos?

19:41.380 --> 19:43.149
Uh, Alpine something
I think.

19:43.149 --> 19:45.418
Yeah, yeah, that's fine.
100 is too much.

19:45.418 --> 19:47.286
- Believe me, he's a cop.
- Listen, man.

19:47.319 --> 19:48.621
I'm about to make
$1,000 here.

19:48.654 --> 19:51.023
Get out of here, huh?

19:52.158 --> 19:55.428
Why do you think
he gives a good deal?

19:55.428 --> 19:58.698
He likes your face?
No, he doesn't.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.133
In the state
of California, USA,

20:01.167 --> 20:03.669
stolen property
more than 950 bucks,

20:03.669 --> 20:06.706
it's grand theft,
felony offense.

20:06.739 --> 20:08.174
- Really?
- Uh-huh.

20:08.174 --> 20:11.444
Maybe you want to make
some money, I know a guy.

20:11.444 --> 20:14.714
Maybe you want to visit prison.
100's a very good price.

20:14.747 --> 20:17.149
(Jakes)
Yo, Mikey.

20:18.184 --> 20:19.452
I got what you need.

20:19.452 --> 20:22.254
Know what?
I miscounted.

20:22.288 --> 20:25.391
I only have nine stereos,
so I'll just take $900.

20:25.424 --> 20:27.326
Okay,
I'll tell you what,

20:27.326 --> 20:29.462
you look like a nice guy
who fell on some hard times,

20:29.462 --> 20:32.064
so I'ma give you that 900,
and I'ma throw in,

20:32.098 --> 20:35.167
like, an extra 50 on some, like,
community service shit,

20:35.167 --> 20:36.168
you feel me,
'cause I like you.

20:36.168 --> 20:37.970
Whoa, whoa,
you know what?

20:38.003 --> 20:39.505
I think I'm gonna pass.

20:39.538 --> 20:41.707
Oh, hold on, hold on, man.
We can make something work out.

20:41.707 --> 20:43.576
Matter of fact,
you're coming with me. I'm LAPD.

20:43.609 --> 20:45.344
Ah! Ah!

20:49.582 --> 20:51.016
[grunts]

20:53.352 --> 20:54.620
[groans]

20:54.653 --> 20:56.288
I'm gonna walk out of here,
okay?

20:56.322 --> 20:59.291
That's not how this works.
Ah!

20:59.325 --> 21:00.760
Okay.

21:09.068 --> 21:11.570
Oh, man!
You were awesome in there!

21:11.604 --> 21:13.339
Just--I had to get out of there,
all right?

21:13.339 --> 21:14.607
Thanks.
Thank you for your help.

21:14.640 --> 21:16.208
I don't really have
too much experience with--

21:16.208 --> 21:18.477
Yeah, yeah, you will learn, man.
I'm Vin.

21:18.511 --> 21:20.212
Hey. Mike.
Listen, man.

21:20.246 --> 21:22.748
Hey, can you really help me
move those stereos?

21:22.748 --> 21:24.183
Yeah, yeah,
I can move your crap.

21:24.216 --> 21:27.453
Uh, maybe a 50% fee.

21:27.486 --> 21:28.621
Hey, you know Kung Fu.

21:28.621 --> 21:30.122
[scoffs]
It's not Kung Fu.

21:30.122 --> 21:32.124
That was freaking cool, man.
How do you learn that shit?

21:32.158 --> 21:34.660
I used to do fight scenes
in movies.

21:34.693 --> 21:36.362
Oh!

21:36.395 --> 21:40.366
Shut up, man.
That's my dream, doing stunts.

21:40.399 --> 21:42.735
Or owning a cruise ship.
Ah.

21:42.968 --> 21:44.103
Hey, Mike.

21:44.136 --> 21:46.505
Hey, uh, so you know
how to shoot a gun?

21:46.505 --> 21:47.506
Yeah.

21:47.540 --> 21:48.507
Okay.

21:48.541 --> 21:52.111
And, uh,
you can jump off buildings?

21:52.111 --> 21:53.512
Yup.

21:53.546 --> 21:56.382
And, uh,
you can blow things up?

21:56.382 --> 21:57.349
Technically.

21:57.383 --> 21:59.718
Excellent, man.

21:59.752 --> 22:01.520
Just come
to my home tomorrow.

22:01.520 --> 22:03.589
I've got some work for you.

22:15.301 --> 22:17.002
(Jakes)
Hot and ready.

22:17.002 --> 22:18.070
(Charlie)
I don't want pancakes, Dale.

22:18.103 --> 22:20.239
From the woman who almost
burnt the house down

22:20.272 --> 22:21.674
trying to get
a decent breakfast.

22:21.707 --> 22:23.342
What's up?

22:23.375 --> 22:26.111
I'm late for my flight,
and I can't find my goddamn ID.

22:26.145 --> 22:29.114
You know, Charlie, if you slept
just a little bit more,

22:29.148 --> 22:30.416
you might not
lose your stuff so easily.

22:30.449 --> 22:31.417
Yeah?

22:31.450 --> 22:33.986
I--okay.

22:34.019 --> 22:36.021
Hey, Mike,
how'd it go with Gusti?

22:36.021 --> 22:39.024
He goes by Vin, actually, and
your plan worked like a charm.

22:39.058 --> 22:40.159
I hope so.

22:40.192 --> 22:41.694
My arm still hurts
from that Bruce Lee shit.

22:41.694 --> 22:44.763
Real case, real problems,
right?

22:44.997 --> 22:46.432
I'm going to see him now,
says he has some work for me.

22:46.432 --> 22:48.100
Hmm.
What kind of work?

22:48.133 --> 22:50.636
Not sure, but I'm getting
in that trunk.

22:50.669 --> 22:53.038
I got it.
I'm out.

22:53.038 --> 22:54.373
Don't you think
your oxy shipment

22:54.406 --> 22:56.141
could wait a day
for you to recoup?

22:56.175 --> 22:58.010
I'm not after the oxy,
I'm after Germaine,

22:58.043 --> 22:59.178
and the quicker
I get this shipment out,

22:59.211 --> 23:00.246
the quicker I get this asshole.

23:00.279 --> 23:02.681
No, thank you,
for the hundredth time.

23:02.715 --> 23:05.050
More of a crepe girl?

23:05.084 --> 23:06.719
Look--
excuse me.

23:06.719 --> 23:08.687
Sorry,
forgot something upstairs.

23:08.721 --> 23:10.723
Briggs, I gotta meet
Carlito, man.

23:10.723 --> 23:14.159
Please tell me
you have a plan.

23:14.193 --> 23:15.227
[sighs]

23:16.328 --> 23:19.331
[tense music]

23:19.365 --> 23:27.373
♪ ♪

23:51.096 --> 23:52.464
Hello?

23:52.498 --> 23:54.366
Hey.
I'm Mike.

23:54.366 --> 23:56.368
[door unlocks]

23:59.571 --> 24:02.074
Gusti, your friend's here.

24:02.107 --> 24:04.076
(Gusti)
I'm coming.

24:04.076 --> 24:06.445
Where you from?

24:06.478 --> 24:08.480
Do you mean in LA
or originally,

24:08.514 --> 24:09.748
or what do you mean?

24:09.748 --> 24:11.617
I'm just trying
to make conversation.

24:11.617 --> 24:13.719
- New York, upstate.
- Huh.

24:13.752 --> 24:14.753
You been to Dutchess County?

24:14.987 --> 24:17.523
I used to go
to a horsemanship camp up there.

24:17.523 --> 24:19.124
Oh, you ride horses?

24:19.124 --> 24:20.592
I used to.

24:20.626 --> 24:22.261
There's plenty of places in LA
you can--

24:22.261 --> 24:25.264
Gusti,
your friend is here!

24:25.264 --> 24:27.533
I'm here.
Hey, how are you, man?

24:27.566 --> 24:29.301
- Good, you?
- Good, good.

24:29.335 --> 24:30.736
This is Madison, my wife.

24:30.970 --> 24:33.305
[scoffs]
Yeah.

24:36.742 --> 24:38.077
What'd you call him?

24:38.110 --> 24:39.111
Gusti.

24:39.111 --> 24:40.179
Gusti.

24:40.212 --> 24:42.648
My Bali name is
Gusti Kadek Pendit.

24:42.681 --> 24:44.116
Can you say that?

24:44.149 --> 24:45.451
Gusti Kalek--

24:45.484 --> 24:49.521
No, man, for white people
it's very hard, okay,

24:49.521 --> 24:51.357
and Vin is
a much cooler name.

24:51.390 --> 24:52.992
Vin short for Gusti?

24:53.025 --> 24:56.395
Um, it's short for Vin Diesel.

24:56.395 --> 24:58.664
There is one movie house
in Manggis, okay,

24:58.697 --> 25:02.334
and we don't have many movies.
but we get xXx.

25:02.368 --> 25:05.537
And I watch it maybe more
than one billion times, man.

25:05.571 --> 25:07.006
[laughs]

25:07.006 --> 25:09.008
Tell me, you did stunts
for that movie?

25:09.041 --> 25:11.744
- No, no, I-I wish.
- Ah! [laughs]

25:11.977 --> 25:13.012
What you cooking, man?

25:13.012 --> 25:14.413
Uh, glycerin.

25:14.413 --> 25:17.416
Come, look.
Look.

25:17.449 --> 25:18.550
Are you boiling dynamite?

25:18.584 --> 25:22.287
Yeah, yeah, just sweating it.

25:22.321 --> 25:23.422
That's how you make glycerin.

25:23.422 --> 25:25.524
Nitroglycerin?

25:25.557 --> 25:28.427
Yeah, he's always
doing something.

25:28.460 --> 25:31.363
You guys know this stuff
is really unstable, right?

25:31.397 --> 25:33.699
The slightest jolt
or jostle--

25:33.732 --> 25:35.000
Boom!

25:35.000 --> 25:36.168
[laughs]

25:37.669 --> 25:41.273
Whoa!
[laughs]

25:41.306 --> 25:44.243
You're right.

25:44.276 --> 25:46.645
You're very calm, man.

25:46.678 --> 25:50.182
You're the expert, I think.

25:50.215 --> 25:51.417
Don't worry, man.

25:51.450 --> 25:54.720
You keep glycerin cold,
and it's much safer.

25:54.720 --> 25:57.322
Don't worry.

25:57.322 --> 25:59.691
Mike, come here.

26:01.326 --> 26:02.995
Hold it.

26:03.028 --> 26:04.596
Okay.

26:04.596 --> 26:05.631
And...

26:07.366 --> 26:11.670
Do...not...move.

26:45.204 --> 26:46.505
[bell dings]

26:51.076 --> 26:54.079
[bell dinging]

27:09.628 --> 27:11.630
Dude, I'm not
blowing up a house.

27:11.663 --> 27:13.999
Not a house,
it's a dentist.

27:13.999 --> 27:15.434
Yeah, I think
something's getting lost

27:15.467 --> 27:16.969
in translation here.

27:20.105 --> 27:22.574
90% of Los Angeles
is illegal immigrant.

27:22.608 --> 27:24.476
- Do you know that?
- I'm sure that's not true.

27:24.510 --> 27:27.446
It is, and because
they're illegal,

27:27.479 --> 27:30.215
maybe men and women,
they don't get real medicine,

27:30.249 --> 27:32.451
so they have to come
to secret places like this,

27:32.484 --> 27:35.187
- and the man here, the dentist?
- Mm-hmm.

27:35.220 --> 27:39.057
He charges little, but he takes
his gold teeth when you sleep.

27:40.259 --> 27:41.527
He steals people's teeth?

27:41.527 --> 27:43.362
Yes.
Bad karma.

27:43.395 --> 27:44.530
Yeah.

27:44.563 --> 27:49.067
He takes it, and he puts them
in this, uh, box.

27:49.101 --> 27:50.202
In the safe?

27:50.235 --> 27:52.538
Yeah, yeah, very safe.

27:52.538 --> 27:54.540
You blow things up.
Blow up this.

27:54.573 --> 27:56.108
Me?

27:56.141 --> 27:58.610
I thought you used
this stuff before.

27:58.644 --> 28:00.546
Yeah, for fishing.

28:00.546 --> 28:02.381
Fishing.

28:02.414 --> 28:04.016
Can you get the teeth or not,
stunt man?

28:04.016 --> 28:07.753
What we gotta do is, we gotta
get the nitro in that crack.

28:07.986 --> 28:11.757
♪ ♪

28:11.990 --> 28:14.560
What?
You have a light bulb?

28:14.560 --> 28:16.995
Yeah, a light bulb.

28:17.029 --> 28:18.030
It's a dentist's office,
right?

28:18.030 --> 28:19.164
Yeah.

28:19.164 --> 28:20.699
So they use this
to make molds of your teeth.

28:20.732 --> 28:24.136
You just add some water.

28:24.136 --> 28:26.171
Stir it up.

28:28.607 --> 28:33.278
And what you get is
a very quick-setting gelatin.

28:33.312 --> 28:41.286
♪ ♪

28:56.568 --> 28:57.669
One good toss.

29:00.038 --> 29:03.609
One, two, three!

29:04.710 --> 29:07.713
[car alarm blaring]

29:07.980 --> 29:10.415
[grunts]

29:10.449 --> 29:12.284
Come on.

29:12.317 --> 29:14.286
[grunts]

29:16.488 --> 29:18.757
[laughs]

29:18.757 --> 29:21.093
Oh, man, so cool.

29:21.093 --> 29:22.227
Vin, come on,
we got to get out of here.

29:22.227 --> 29:24.329
I think the whole neighborhood
heard us.

29:24.363 --> 29:27.666
[chuckles]
Jackpot.

29:35.607 --> 29:37.643
(Tuturro)
All right, man,
the Caza cartel owns, what,

29:37.643 --> 29:39.211
20% of the Mexican corridor?

29:39.211 --> 29:40.212
Yes, sir.

29:40.245 --> 29:42.147
If we just hand them
over the territory--

29:42.180 --> 29:44.149
Well, then Caza becomes
the most powerful cartel

29:44.182 --> 29:46.318
this side of Colombia,
yeah.

29:46.351 --> 29:47.486
And you're good with this?

29:47.519 --> 29:50.355
No, I hate it, but I owed
Alfredo Armas a favor.

29:54.126 --> 29:56.662
How's it work, man,
logistically?

29:56.662 --> 29:58.997
All right, all you gotta do
is get Lucia.

29:59.031 --> 29:59.998
Caza takes care of the rest.

30:00.032 --> 30:01.233
Now, the only problem

30:01.266 --> 30:02.968
is that the place is gonna be
lousy with Mexicanos,

30:02.968 --> 30:04.603
so in order for you
to stand out--

30:04.636 --> 30:06.371
I gotta be waving
the white flag.

30:06.405 --> 30:08.373
Damn right.
Strap that to your ride.

30:08.407 --> 30:11.410
Caza foot soldiers
should let you through.

30:13.011 --> 30:16.214
I don't want nobody else dying
'cause of me, Briggs.

30:16.248 --> 30:18.383
Look, Johnny, this beef
between Caza and the Solanos,

30:18.417 --> 30:19.451
it's been going on
for years, man.

30:19.484 --> 30:21.253
The war has nothing
to do with you.

30:21.253 --> 30:23.522
You're doing
the right thing.

30:23.555 --> 30:25.190
You know what,
someday I'm gonna learn

30:25.223 --> 30:26.992
how to rationalize things
the way you do.

30:27.025 --> 30:27.993
White flag, okay?

30:28.026 --> 30:29.494
See you on the other side,
man.

30:29.528 --> 30:37.502
♪ ♪

30:47.412 --> 30:50.549
(Tuturro)
Jesus Christ, man.

30:50.549 --> 30:52.217
I'm not so pretty now,
am I?

30:52.250 --> 30:54.986
Carlito, what happened
to you, man?

30:55.020 --> 30:56.421
Don't pretend like
you weren't there.

30:56.455 --> 31:00.225
No, I don't mean your face,
man, I mean you.

31:00.258 --> 31:02.227
How'd you get so messed up
in the head, man?

31:02.260 --> 31:05.397
I mean, your dad was tough,
but, shit, he was all right.

31:05.430 --> 31:06.998
What's that, your mama take you
off the titty too early?

31:07.032 --> 31:08.433
Silencio!

31:08.433 --> 31:11.203
You know what, Johnny?

31:11.236 --> 31:13.405
I don't think I'm having fun
with you anymore.

31:13.438 --> 31:16.441
Your dad ran the cartel
for 20 years.

31:16.441 --> 31:18.643
You got the keys to the kingdom
for less than a month,

31:18.677 --> 31:20.579
and shit's crumbling down,
I mean, shit.

31:20.579 --> 31:23.048
Look around.
I don't see anything crumbling.

31:23.048 --> 31:27.586
Not everything that's happening
is happening in front of you.

31:27.586 --> 31:28.587
[chuckles]

31:28.587 --> 31:30.589
Huh.

31:30.589 --> 31:32.457
[gunshots and men yelling]

31:32.457 --> 31:34.059
Qué fue eso?

31:34.092 --> 31:37.129
[machine gunfire]

31:42.134 --> 31:45.504
[shouting in Spanish]

31:45.537 --> 31:48.039
[gunfire continues]

31:48.039 --> 31:51.376
[shouting in Spanish]

31:55.313 --> 31:56.281
Johnny.

31:59.651 --> 32:01.219
It's time to go, baby.

32:01.253 --> 32:02.988
[gasps]
Johnny!

32:05.624 --> 32:08.293
Oh, shit!
Go, go, go.

32:13.398 --> 32:14.499
Pop the hood, pop the hood.

32:14.499 --> 32:20.005
♪ ♪

32:20.038 --> 32:21.206
Johnny, look out!

32:23.608 --> 32:24.576
Leaving so soon?

32:24.609 --> 32:27.579
[tense music]

32:27.612 --> 32:35.587
♪ ♪

32:55.006 --> 32:57.742
You remember when
we were children, hermanita?

32:57.976 --> 33:00.212
You remember the piñon tree?

33:00.245 --> 33:03.081
I used to love that tree.

33:03.114 --> 33:06.051
One day, Johnny,
she decides to climb to the top.

33:06.084 --> 33:09.054
I told her no,
it is too dangerous,

33:09.087 --> 33:10.121
but she just laughs.

33:10.121 --> 33:12.757
There she goes,
all the way to the top

33:12.991 --> 33:15.994
like a little changuita.

33:17.529 --> 33:19.364
And then all of a sudden...
[slams fist]

33:19.397 --> 33:21.533
The bough breaks,
and she falls 50 feet.

33:21.566 --> 33:23.401
I was sure
she had snapped her neck,

33:23.401 --> 33:24.603
but no, she springs up.

33:24.636 --> 33:25.637
She's just fine.

33:25.670 --> 33:27.138
Gonna tell me where to go,

33:27.172 --> 33:28.673
or you just want me
to keep driving or what?

33:28.707 --> 33:31.510
My father, he beat me
with a riding crop

33:31.543 --> 33:36.248
when he found out, and he had
the piñon tree chopped down.

33:36.281 --> 33:38.216
You asked me what happened,
Johnny.

33:38.250 --> 33:40.252
She happened.

33:42.420 --> 33:45.123
You see, she takes
every single thing that I love,

33:45.156 --> 33:47.025
and she chops it down.

33:47.058 --> 33:49.361
I don't care about the drugs,
the money.

33:49.394 --> 33:50.629
I don't care about Father.

33:50.662 --> 33:54.299
No, the only thing that matters
is that Lucia...

33:54.299 --> 33:55.700
[cocks gun]

33:55.700 --> 34:00.572
Spends her final breath
knowing that I won.

34:00.605 --> 34:03.141
Carlito.

34:03.174 --> 34:05.710
You talk too much, man.

34:05.710 --> 34:07.012
[tires screech]

34:31.269 --> 34:33.438
You piece of shit!

34:33.438 --> 34:35.140
[grunts]

34:35.173 --> 34:38.176
[both grunting]

34:39.711 --> 34:41.413
That's enough, that's enough,
that's enough.

34:41.446 --> 34:43.214
Eternity in hell
isn't enough!

34:43.214 --> 34:44.583
[spits]

34:44.616 --> 34:46.051
That's a good boy,
Johnny.

34:46.084 --> 34:48.486
"That's a good boy,
Johnny"?

34:48.486 --> 34:51.456
"That's a good boy, Johnny"?
"Good boy, Johnny"?

34:51.489 --> 34:52.624
- Huh?
- Shoot him.

34:52.624 --> 34:53.625
Huh? Huh?

34:53.658 --> 34:55.226
Shoot him.

34:55.260 --> 34:57.629
Kill him, Johnny, please.

34:57.629 --> 35:00.098
- Kill him, Johnny, please.
- "Good boy, Johnny"?

35:00.131 --> 35:01.299
(Lucia)
Please!

35:01.333 --> 35:03.301
- [shouts]
- [laughs]

35:05.737 --> 35:09.407
That ain't my job.
That ain't my job.

35:09.441 --> 35:11.242
Nah.

35:12.744 --> 35:14.546
We'll see how you like
living in a cage.

35:14.579 --> 35:16.615
You're under arrest.

35:16.615 --> 35:19.451
No, you don't have jurisdiction
in Mexico.

35:19.484 --> 35:22.687
U.S. border's
right there.

35:22.721 --> 35:24.155
We can walk.

35:49.147 --> 35:53.251
When I thought I was gonna
die in that room,

35:53.251 --> 35:55.620
I realized
I never even had a life.

35:58.289 --> 36:00.525
I've always been
my father's daughter

36:00.558 --> 36:03.762
or my brother's sister,
a Solano.

36:03.995 --> 36:05.697
Now you can be
whatever you want to be.

36:05.697 --> 36:08.166
- No, I can't.
- You can.

36:08.199 --> 36:12.003
You get to go home and
put on a badge and be a hero.

36:12.003 --> 36:14.472
I would have killed
my own brother.

36:17.042 --> 36:19.611
If that's not being a Solano,
then I don't know what is.

36:24.149 --> 36:25.150
We would never work.

36:25.183 --> 36:26.418
- Don't say that.
- You know that.

36:26.451 --> 36:28.019
Don't say that. Don't say that.
Don't say that.

36:28.019 --> 36:30.522
Johnny, I'm sorry, but--

36:30.555 --> 36:33.491
[thunder]

36:36.061 --> 36:39.164
I will do anything
you ask me to, okay?

36:39.197 --> 36:41.099
- Okay?
- Please don't.

36:41.132 --> 36:43.468
[sobs]
Don't.

36:53.178 --> 36:57.549
What you, uh--
what you gonna do now?

36:59.084 --> 37:01.052
I still haven't seen
the Southern Cross.

37:01.086 --> 37:03.154
[laughs]

37:03.188 --> 37:04.489
Yeah, me neither.

37:07.225 --> 37:11.129
You're the greatest man
that I've ever known, Johnny.

37:11.162 --> 37:12.997
I hope you know that.

37:14.733 --> 37:16.434
Yup.

37:16.468 --> 37:19.003
(man)
Miss, it's time to go.

37:27.445 --> 37:30.482
[thunder]

37:43.094 --> 37:46.097
What do you think?

37:46.097 --> 37:48.199
Same, right?

37:50.168 --> 37:51.136
Looks even.

37:51.169 --> 37:54.038
Good.
So here is your half.

37:54.072 --> 37:58.076
Worth about $100 each,
I think.

37:58.109 --> 38:00.078
How much did
that dynamite cost?

38:00.078 --> 38:02.413
$200.
Thank you for reminding me.

38:02.447 --> 38:04.282
You owe me 100 bucks.

38:07.485 --> 38:08.686
I'll see you around.

38:08.720 --> 38:12.490
Yeah, yeah, we're gonna be
good friends, man.

38:12.524 --> 38:13.491
Yeah.

38:13.525 --> 38:14.492
Take care.

38:14.526 --> 38:16.461
Yup.

38:18.696 --> 38:26.704
♪ ♪

38:56.668 --> 38:59.637
[dramatic music]

38:59.671 --> 39:07.645
♪ ♪

39:19.691 --> 39:23.494
[camera shutter clicks]

39:23.528 --> 39:26.497
[rock music]

39:26.531 --> 39:29.567
[crowd chatter]

39:29.567 --> 39:31.502
(Briggs)
And she's back, just in time.

39:31.536 --> 39:33.137
Straight from the airport.

39:33.171 --> 39:35.106
I love you more than my bed.
Know that.

39:35.139 --> 39:36.107
Love you too.
Love you too.

39:36.140 --> 39:37.575
And that's why
we love you.

39:37.609 --> 39:39.177
Thank you.

39:39.177 --> 39:42.146
To our beloved J.T.,
the only one of us

39:42.180 --> 39:44.115
in too damn long
who actually put cuffs

39:44.148 --> 39:45.283
on the guy he was chasing.

39:45.316 --> 39:46.584
Thank you for your help, man.
Thank you.

39:46.618 --> 39:47.719
John boy.

39:47.752 --> 39:49.454
- Hey.
- Johnny, cheers.

39:49.454 --> 39:51.022
To--to me.

39:51.055 --> 39:52.323
[laughs]

39:52.323 --> 39:53.658
So wait, am I the only one
that thinks

39:53.691 --> 39:55.293
this kid needs to get
back on the horse?

39:55.326 --> 39:57.595
Like, make Lucia
a distant-ass memory?

39:57.595 --> 39:59.130
Oh, John boy,

39:59.163 --> 40:01.733
she's been checking you out
all night long, man.

40:01.733 --> 40:03.635
[chuckles]
No, no, no, I'm good.

40:03.668 --> 40:05.169
(Jakes)
Ah, he thought about it.

40:05.169 --> 40:07.372
Your heart needs time to heal,
is that what's up?

40:07.405 --> 40:08.506
It's too soon, man.

40:08.539 --> 40:10.708
Well, time heals
some wounds.

40:10.742 --> 40:13.011
Tequila-fueled casual sex
heals others.

40:13.044 --> 40:15.480
Well, I can't provide you
with casual sex,

40:15.480 --> 40:18.182
but I can get some tequila,
on me.

40:18.216 --> 40:21.419
Hey.
Got a minute?

40:23.454 --> 40:24.555
What's up?

40:24.589 --> 40:26.491
You still want to help out
with the Sarkissians?

40:26.524 --> 40:29.093
Of course.
Colby was my fault, so--

40:29.093 --> 40:30.495
Colby was not your fault,
Paige.

40:30.495 --> 40:31.696
That's debatable.

40:31.729 --> 40:33.698
I burned the wrong fingers,
Paul.

40:33.731 --> 40:35.767
Okay, so what's the plan?

40:35.767 --> 40:39.437
Well, Ari has been supplanted
by Toros Berbarian.

40:39.470 --> 40:40.672
I want to work you
under with him,

40:40.705 --> 40:42.307
so that when
Tevan Adamian dies--

40:42.340 --> 40:43.675
We've got somebody
on the inside,

40:43.708 --> 40:46.477
whether it's Toros or Ari
that gets the promotion.

40:46.477 --> 40:48.613
- [clicks tongue]
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm down.

40:48.613 --> 40:49.614
All right.

40:49.614 --> 40:51.015
Hey, it's Serpico.

40:51.049 --> 40:52.750
- Yo.
- Oh, Mikey's here.

40:52.750 --> 40:54.319
What's up, playa?

40:54.352 --> 40:55.420
(Jakes)
About time.

40:55.453 --> 40:56.988
Oh, I'm sorry I'm late.

40:56.988 --> 40:58.523
Hey, why don't I buy
the next round, huh?

40:58.523 --> 40:59.724
Bring 'em on.

40:59.757 --> 41:01.726
- Can I borrow you for a second?
- Yeah.

41:01.759 --> 41:03.461
All right, now--

41:07.131 --> 41:09.233
Well, I was right, Briggs,

41:09.267 --> 41:11.269
and this thing is bigger
than I could have ever imagined.

41:11.269 --> 41:12.470
What do you got, Mikey?

41:12.470 --> 41:14.739
It's a Soviet CW unit.

41:14.973 --> 41:17.642
We're talking mustard gas,
lewisite, VX.

41:17.675 --> 41:20.044
If you had to ask me,
it's sarin.

41:20.078 --> 41:23.348
Your kid is rolling around
with a WMD in his trunk.

41:23.381 --> 41:25.984
You know, I just spent the day
with this kid, Briggs,

41:26.017 --> 41:28.653
and I don't think Gusti has
any idea what he's sitting on.

41:28.686 --> 41:30.488
What the hell is he doing
with that?

41:30.521 --> 41:32.657
[sighs]

41:32.690 --> 41:35.259
I think the better question is,

41:35.259 --> 41:38.262
who the hell is he
supposed to deliver this to?

42:06.257 --> 42:08.659
[dog barks]
